race.comment: CHILLI REAPER (5) is a lightly raced mare resuming for her second campaign. She did some nice things in four runs there and has won a trial leading in. This looks a very winnable race. THE WIZARD KING (1) can mix his form, awful two back at Wodonga but not beaten far at Mornington when rolling along in front. Drawn to effect here, he can bounce to the front and give a sight. SHOUT ME (4) notched up his maiden victory at Hamilton last time and finds a suitable race to measure up in. SUNDAY FUN DAY (3) will be fitter off a solid return at Pooncarie. This isn't any easier but he's in the mix on an each way basis.
